latestIgtvVideos.title: 🌙✨Moonstar by The Sass Bar🌙✨
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
The Moonstar was conceptualised with the commitment to being a clean, sustainable and transparent brand. The focus is on essential oils and plant derivatives for their healing and beneficial properties. These essential oils are usda certified. The plant derivatives are all natural such as carrot puree, almond milk, coconut milk, charcoal powder, matcha etc. We are also committed to making this using sustainable ingredients and packaging.
.
Launching the first three in this line. We have already done a soft launch on our website and we received an incredible feedback and response. We hope you love this and replace your plastic body wash with this beautiful range ✨

latestIgtvVideos.title: Making & Cutting - 🍉 Ombré Watermelon Soap
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Are you even a soap maker if you never made watermelon soap ? 😂 For the longest time I never made one because everyone has made a watermelon soap. My super lovely brother who I always run to for advice and suggestions came to me one day and said why don’t you make a watermelon soap ? I explained to him it’s nothing new I would be doing. So he said I’m sure you will think of something to make it interesting.

That’s where the ombré technique comes in and oh boy - it’s been quite a seller.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Using our Shampoo Bar
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
So this baby has been under the works for several months - I did a lot of research on not only shampoos but also shampoo bars available in the market world over. 
I personally used them for several months and gave them to friends and family so I could get as much feedback as possible. .
.
Two things I felt always after using the best of shampoos that my hair didn’t feel fully clean. With this shampoo bar - I find my scalp and hair to be clean - if you know what I mean.
Second, my hair stayed non-greasy for a longer time which saves me from washing my hair every 2 days.
I also noticed volume/shine/ non-frizzy hair after the 1st wash itself.

There are lots of shampoos available in the market and well even working for your hair but do give this one a try as it lasts about 40-50 washes and that means saving about 3 shampoo bottles from touching the surface of this earth :)
